      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STAR PEDRO (1) has mixed form a little and missed the frame the last two but was a Grade 5 winner three back (23.04) at this track over 401m. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. TYSON CREEK (3) is progressing well with another good run, placing by 5 lengths (21.05) in a Grade 5 at Nowra. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Leading player again. PEARL'S WAY (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (23.34) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Leading chance. CORLESS DEVIOUS (8) was a surprise last-start placegetter worth considering.",
